    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>An inner interface has to be static in order to be accessed. The interface isn't associated with instances of the class, but with the class itself, so it would be accessed with <code>Foo.Bar</code>, like so:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Baz implements Foo.Bar {\n   ...\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In most ways, this isn't different from a static inner class.</p>\n"
  }, {
