      "creation_date" : 1331731640,
      "post_id" : 209158,
      "comment_id" : 12331665,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I know this is an old topic, but I would prefer the outer class to be in it&#39;s own package and any supplementary interfaces (e.g. <code>Map.Entry</code>) or classes to also be within that package. I say this because I like to keep my classes short and to the point. Also a reader can see what other entities are related to a class by looking at the classes in the package. I&#39;d probably have a package <code>java.collections.map</code> for maps. This is about OO and modularity. <code>java.util</code> has too much in it. <code>util</code> is like <code>common</code> - a smell IMO"
